<p>I have these tables  </p>  <pre><code> id | tests    | results   001 | testId_1 | 1   001 | testId_2 | 1   002 | testId_1 | 1   003 | testId_2 | 1   004 | testId_1 | 1   004 | testId_2 | 1   </code></pre>  <p>and </p>  <pre><code>test_id | tests      1234 | testId_1      4565 | testId_2   </code></pre>  <p>Is there a way to combine them to create a new table with <code>NULL</code> value for those <code>id</code>s that are missing a <code>testId_x</code> like so  </p>  <pre><code> id | tests    | results   001 | testId_1 | 1   001 | testId_2 | 1   002 | testId_1 | 1   002 | testId_2 | NULL     003 | testId_1 | NULL   003 | testId_2 | 1   004 | testId_1 | 1   004 | testId_2 | 1   </code></pre>